Additional PlankaC License Notes
================================

These notes do not replace or narrow the MIT License above. They explain how
the license is intended to apply inside this repository.

Project Scope
-------------

The MIT License applies to the PlankaC project files in this repository,
including:

- the PlankaC parser, source loader, runtime, bytecode writer, CLI, and public
  C API under `c/`;
- the bundled PlankaMath calculator and Windows GUI host;
- the `.plk` source plans under `src/`, `examples/`, and `tests`;
- the conformance fixtures and test runner;
- the project documentation and build scripts;
- small auxiliary source files such as the 8086 assembly note under `asm/`.

Rights Granted
--------------

You may use PlankaC for personal, educational, research, open-source, or
commercial work. You may copy it, modify it, build it, link it into your own C
programs, publish modified versions, distribute source or binary builds, and
use the `.plk` examples as a starting point for your own Plankalkuel-inspired
programs.

Embedding And Reuse
-------------------

The public PlankaC API in `c/plankac.h` may be embedded in other C or C++
programs under the same MIT terms. A host application may load the default
`.plk` plans or its own source list. The license does not require your program
to be open source, but any distributed copy of PlankaC code must keep the MIT
copyright notice and permission notice.

Source Plans And Examples
-------------------------

The `.plk` files in this repository are licensed as part of the project. You
may study, copy, adapt, and redistribute them. If you publish a project based
on these files, keep the license notice somewhere reasonable in the source
distribution, documentation, or about/license screen.

Generated Files
---------------

Bytecode files, binaries, object files, static libraries, and other build
outputs generated from this repository may be used and distributed under the
MIT terms, provided the required license notice is included when PlankaC code
or a substantial portion of it is distributed.

Historical References
---------------------

The bibliography, names of historical works, and references to Konrad Zuse's
Plankalkuel are provided for attribution and study. This license covers this
repository's own code, documentation, and examples. It does not claim ownership
over historical texts, papers, names, or external archived documents cited by
the project.

No Warranty
-----------

PlankaC is a small educational implementation of a linear Plankalkuel-inspired
profile. It is not a complete historical Plankalkuel implementation and is not
provided with any warranty of correctness, fitness, safety, performance, or
compatibility. Use it, extend it, and verify it for your own context.

Names And Endorsement
---------------------

The names PlankaC and PlankaMath identify this project and its bundled
calculator host. The MIT License lets you reuse the code, but it does not imply
that modified versions are endorsed by the original project contributors.
